{"id":"355t","title":"Add sg context command for full context dump","description":"Implement sg context \u003cid\u003e command that outputs full saga context for agents. Include: saga details (title, description, status, priority, labels), parent/child tree, dependencies with status (blocking vs complete), related sagas, recent history. Add --format json flag for machine-readable output. This enables agents to understand the full context of a saga including relationships and blockers.","status":"done","priority":"high","claimed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","created_at":"2026-02-26T11:28:47.783820264Z","updated_at":"2026-02-26T11:32:25.592292126Z","history":[{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:28:47.783820264Z","action":"created","note":"Saga created"},{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:28:58.617748554Z","action":"priority_changed","note":"normal -\u003e high"},{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:32:25.592291656Z","action":"status_changed","note":"active -\u003e done"}]}
{"id":"2ma5","title":"Create agent skill for saga integration","description":"Create an OpenClaw agent skill that teaches agents how to use saga effectively. The skill should cover: reading sagas for context (sg status, sg list, sg search), creating sagas for new work (sg new), logging progress (sg log), updating status (sg done, sg continue), checking dependencies before completion, using sg context for full context dumps. The goal is making saga the interface between human planning and agent execution. Agents should check saga context before acting and update sagas as work progresses.","status":"done","priority":"high","claimed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","created_at":"2026-02-26T11:28:54.413831339Z","updated_at":"2026-02-26T11:36:57.653749232Z","history":[{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:28:54.413831339Z","action":"created","note":"Saga created"},{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:28:58.625157578Z","action":"priority_changed","note":"normal -\u003e high"},{"timestamp":"2026-02-26T11:36:57.6537483Z","action":"status_changed","note":"active -\u003e done"}]}
